From: Daniil Tatianin <d-tatianin@yandex-team.ru>
Date: Thu, 16 Mar 2023 13:29:21 +0300
Subject: qed/qed_sriov: guard against NULL derefs from qed_iov_get_vf_info
Patch-mainline: v6.3-rc4
Git-commit: 25143b6a01d0cc5319edd3de22ffa2578b045550
References: jsc#SLE-19001

We have to make sure that the info returned by the helper is valid
before using it.

Found by Linux Verification Center (linuxtesting.org) with the SVACE
static analysis tool.

Fixes: f990c82c385b ("qed*: Add support for ndo_set_vf_trust")
Fixes: 733def6a04bf ("qed*: IOV link control")
Signed-off-by: Daniil Tatianin <d-tatianin@yandex-team.ru>
Reviewed-by: Michal Swiatkowski <michal.swiatkowski@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/qed/qed_sriov.c |    5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/qed/qed_sriov.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/qed/qed_sriov.c
@@ -4404,6 +4404,9 @@ qed_iov_configure_min_tx_rate(struct qed
 	}
 
 	vf = qed_iov_get_vf_info(QED_LEADING_HWFN(cdev), (u16)vfid, true);
+	if (!vf)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
 	vport_id = vf->vport_id;
 
 	return qed_configure_vport_wfq(cdev, vport_id, rate);
@@ -5152,7 +5155,7 @@ static void qed_iov_handle_trust_change(
 
 		/* Validate that the VF has a configured vport */
 		vf = qed_iov_get_vf_info(hwfn, i, true);
-		if (!vf->vport_instance)
+		if (!vf || !vf->vport_instance)
 			continue;
 
 		memset(&params, 0, sizeof(params));
